üíôüíôüíô By- @estellemaskame
üíôüíôüíô When a 16 year old Eden Muruno agreed to spend her summer with her estranged father in the city of Santa Monica, California. She  has no idea what she is letting herself into. Eden's parents are divorced and gone through their separate ways and now her father has a brand new family. For Eden it's like she is about to meet her three step Brothers. Eldest of them is Tyler, a troubled teenager, short tempered and huge ego. Complete polar opposites Eden finds herself incomplete full of new experience, where Tyler's friends take her in their wing. But one thing she just can't understand is Tyler. And the more she presses to figure out the truth about him, more she finds herself falling for the one person she shouldn't ------ her stepbrother. 
Throw in Tyler's clingy girlfriend, and a guy who has set his eyes on Eden, and there is lies, secrets and a whole of a drama. But how can Eden keep her feelings under control? 
And she ever work out the truth of Tyler??
üíôüíôüíô

BOOK REVIEW!!
QOTD: What is relationships to you?
MA:- For me it is Love, Care, Efforts, Value, Respect ‚ù§Ô∏è
"SOMETIMES IT IS THE ONE WHO LOVES YOU HURTS YOU THE MOST"
Trying to write this review for the second time. I don't know when, I've written it for the first time. I was so emotional and I wasn't even able to speak about it. But now after 3 days, after starting a new book and after watching a tons of YouTube videos. I think I am ready to write.(and you're probably reading itüòÇ) So "IT ENDS WITH US"  @colleenhoover What does a title sounds to you?? Don't raise your expectations because it's the opposite..
Well it is used in the book and it has a meaning. But not what your thinking.
Anyways I picked up this book because this title had attracted me so much. It definitely has a love story. Of course! 
But it's not the love story like, where you get all the flowers and happy stuff. It's not like where the guy meet the girl, they fall in love, and Happily Ever After!! Nahh if you are looking for this kind of story in this book,  that's really wrong place. 
This is a story which only have truths or I must say "Naked Truths".
It's a real story which is about the empowerment of the women. How women should take stand for themselves as well for their children if needed. Women doesn't need men to take care of themselves. They can do it by their own. Women are very strong. That's all about women empowerment, you will get to know when you read the book.
At last....
I just want to say sometimes if you love someone you have to let them go. For your own good. And love is not the only thing that keep the relationships going.
And Obviously, do I need to say that I love the book so much‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è she has written so nicelyüòç 
Also, there is gonna be a movie soonüòçwhich I'm very grateful to @justinbaldoni because he brought the rights of the movie‚ù§Ô∏è Thanks alot @justinbaldoni ‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏èüíØ

BOOK REVIEW!!!
MARRY ME STRANGER (BOOK-1 OF STRANGER TRILOGY)
.
.
. He has no voice, no face, no name, no identity, but he has an intention...
I'm Rivahna Banerjee young and independent girl living in Mumbai alone. My parents love me, my boyfriend adores me, and I have a great job.
But here's the thing my life is in danger: someone's been following me around watching my every move, trying to get control of my life.
At first I thought it is a cheap prank trying to get my attention. My roommate suggested that he must be a Secret  admire. What he doesn't know is the police have set a trap knob him.

BOOK REVIEW!!
QOTD~ Can you fall in love with a prostitute??
AOTD~ Yes there is no shame in this. If someone loves you with whole heart and ready to leave the past behind. There is no shame in falling in love whether it's a prostitute or a criminal.
It is both for me fiction and Non-fiction.
Eleven Minutes tells the story of Maria, a young girl from a Brazilian village whose first innocent brushes with love, leave her heartbroken. At  a tender age she becomes convinced that you will never find true love instead believing that "Love Is A terrible thing that will make you suffer....." A chance of meeting in Rio takes her to Geneva where she dreams of finding Fame and fortune yet ends up working as a prostitute....
In  Geneva Maria drift further and further away from Love while at the same time developing fascination for sex. Eventually Maria's trespassing new view of love is put to test when she mets a handsome young painter. In this odyssey of self-discovery Maria has to choose between pursuing the path of Darkness,sexual pleasure for its own sake, Or risking everything to find her own "inner light" and possibility of sacred sex, sex in the context of love. In this gripping and daring novel @paulocoelho  sensitively explores the sacred nature of sex and love and invites us to confront our own prejudices and demons and embrace our own "inner light"
I loved this book so muchüòçüòç It was my first @paulocoelho
Novel . I'm so impressed by his writing style and also The way he has narrated this story‚ù§Ô∏è To be honest I wasn't expecting this book to be so much detailed about prostitution, love, sex, pain and suffering and pleasure. The way he has explained everything,  So nicely and so easily. It was an eye opener for me! Also this book explains the history of prostitution and the term called ' Sacred Sex'. It explains the desires and needs and difference between love and lust too. It has an detailed information about Man and Woman. And he didn't disappointed me with the ending üòÇ‚ù§Ô∏è ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê/‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê
Recommend~ Totally if you're interested‚ù§Ô∏è

BOOK REVIEWWW!!
THE GIRL ON THE TRAIN BY @paulahawkins2010 
Everyday is same. Until today!!!
It is a story of a girl name Rachel she catches same commuter train every morning. She knows it will wait at the same signal it's time each time overlooking a row of back gardens. She will started to feel like she knows the people who live in in one of the houses. Their life as she sees is perfect. If only Rachel could be that happy. And then she sees something shocking, and in one moment everything changes. Now Rachel have a chance to become a part of their lives which she only watched from afar. Now they will see she is much more then just a girl on the train...
I loved this book so much‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§ It's chock-full of chilling twists. The narration is done perfectly. The plot twist is is not expected. The language used is simple and the story really takes a confusing turn.  You are desperate to know the end. I even tried too read the endüòÇ Lucky I stopped myself üòÇ It's the debut novel of her. All the other characters POV is narrated nicely. 
It's definitely a must read book for all the thirller, mystery lovers like meüòç 
And back story: I've waited so long to take this picture. I don't travel in trains much. I finally gotta chance to do that... After i took picture. I finally read this book in peaceüòÇ
And also I WAS THE ONLY GIRL ON THE TRAIN.... Scary isn't it??

BOOKKKKK REVIEW..
@sudeepnagarkar
IT STARTED WITH A FRIEND REQUEST ‚ù§
It is a story of of a guy named Akash. He's  single, he has a good job, he is looking looking for a girlwith brains over miniskirts. One night he goes to bar with his  friend Aditya. He give the challenge to him to go talk to a girl. He was shy at first but then drinks take over his mind. And he  falls in love at first sight with Aleesha. She  shares her Bmm pin with him, and they started to talk regularly. And The Bmm pin Cupid in their story. They both are in love as his friend Aditya helps Aakash to propose Aleesha.
Where on another side Aleesha's  dad's friend daughter Tamanna is an introvert. She had to share room with Aleesha. As she  shifts from Kolkata to Mumbai. She had a  huge crush Deep her colleague
Will Tamanna able to confess her feelings towards Deep?
What happens when a misfortune strikes in Aakash and Aleesha's story? 
Will love survive or Will it tear them apart?
I'm absolutely surprised and in love with this book‚ù§‚ù§
The thing I was least expecting in the story to happen. Was the great plot Twist of this book.
If I say more I will ruin this book for you guys....
It's  better to read by your own.
Some of my  favourite lines from this book
"If you truly love someone and destined to meet then you just need to hang in there and wait for the right moment."üòç
"As a couple you will have to go through life various struggles, but in end everything pass. And if it doesn't it's not the end."‚ù§
"It started with a Friend Request...........
And life was never the same again!"‚ù§

I don‚Äôt know from where should I start. This book was gifted me as my birthday gift (basically I chose it they paidüòÇ) It is a story about Dhruv and Aryana. As she grew up people started to stay away from her because they thought it‚Äôs contagious. Later on when she went to school she met a boy named Dhruv. He was the one who understood her.
